04/11/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Belgian Prime Minister Guy Verhofstadt arrived on an official visit Monday (3 November) to Ankara, and said a powerful NATO member such as Turkey should play an active role in Europe's common defence system. 
He urged the government to focus on the Copenhagen political criteria, human rights and democracy, in an effort open EU accession negotiations.
In other news Monday, Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said relations with the United States have settled to what he described as their natural position. 
In a speech to a parliamentary committee, he said the government remains committed to strengthening co-operation with Washington. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, Milliyet - 03/11/03)
